                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./136:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Vice
                        Consul at Nassau</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Points</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-01T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Pan American Airways which has been awarded contract by Post Office Department
                    for carrying mail from Key West to Panama Canal Zone and from Key West to Porto
                    Rico is contemplating bidding for contract between Miami and Nassau. Mr. John A.
                    Hambleton, Vice President of the Company, is in Nassau in connection with this
                    matter. Please render him all proper assistance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
